#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:133
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use the `exec` Statement in Wrapper Scripts"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:136
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If the port installs a shell script whose purpose is to launch another "
"program, and if launching that program is the last action performed by the "
"script, make sure to launch the program using the `exec` statement, for "
"instance:"
msgstr ""
"Si el puerto instala un script de shell cuyo propósito es iniciar otro "
"programa, y si el lanzamiento de ese programa es la última acción realizada "
"por el script, asegúrese de iniciar el programa utilizando el "
"<function>exec</function> declaración, por ejemplo:"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:141
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"#!/bin/sh\n"
"exec %%LOCALBASE%%/bin/java -jar %%DATADIR%%/foo.jar \"$@\"\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:144
msgid ""
"The `exec` statement replaces the shell process with the specified program. "
"If `exec` is omitted, the shell process remains in memory while the program "
"is executing, and needlessly consumes system resources."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "Do Things Rationally"
msgstr "Hacer las cosas de forma racional"

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:149
msgid ""
"The [.filename]#Makefile# should do things in a simple and reasonable "
"manner. Making it a couple of lines shorter or more readable is always "
"better. Examples include using a make `.if` construct instead of a shell "
"`if` construct, not redefining `do-extract` if redefining `EXTRACT*` is "
"enough, and using `GNU_CONFIGURE` instead of `CONFIGURE_ARGS += --prefix="
"${PREFIX}`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:151
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If a lot of new code is needed to do something, there may already be an "
"implementation of it in [.filename]#bsd.port.mk#. While hard to read, there "
"are a great many seemingly-hard problems for which [.filename]#bsd.port.mk# "
"already provides a shorthand solution."
msgstr ""
"Si se necesita mucho código nuevo para hacer algo, es posible que ya exista "
"una implementación en <filename>bsd.port.mk</filename>.Si bien es difícil de "
"leer, hay muchos problemas aparentemente difíciles para los que <filename>bsd"
".port.mk</filename> ya proporciona una solución taquigráfica."

#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:153
#, no-wrap
msgid "Respect Both `CC` and `CXX`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:156
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The port must respect both `CC` and `CXX`. What we mean by this is that the "
"port must not set the values of these variables absolutely, overriding "
"existing values; instead, it may append whatever values it needs to the "
"existing values. This is so that build options that affect all ports can be "
"set globally."
msgstr ""
"El puerto debe respetar <varname>CFLAGS</varname>. Lo que queremos decir con "
"esto es que el puerto no debe establecer el valor de esta variable en "
"absoluto, anulando el valor existente. En su lugar, puede agregar los "
"valores que necesite al valor existente. Esto es para que las opciones de "
"construcción que afectan a todos los puertos se puedan configurar "
"globalmente."

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:158
msgid ""
"If the port does not respect these variables, please add `NO_PACKAGE=ignores "
"either cc or cxx` to the [.filename]#Makefile#."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:160
msgid ""
"Here is an example of a [.filename]#Makefile# respecting both `CC` and "
"`CXX`. Note the `?=`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:164
#, no-wrap
msgid "CC?= gcc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:169
#, no-wrap
msgid "CXX?= g++\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:172
msgid "Here is an example which respects neither `CC` nor `CXX`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:176
#, no-wrap
msgid "CC= gcc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:181
#, no-wrap
msgid "CXX= g++\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:184
msgid ""
"Both `CC` and `CXX` can be defined on FreeBSD systems in [.filename]#/etc/"
"make.conf#. The first example defines a value if it was not previously set "
"in [.filename]#/etc/make.conf#, preserving any system-wide definitions. The "
"second example clobbers anything previously defined."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:186
#, no-wrap
msgid "Respect `CFLAGS`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:189
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The port must respect `CFLAGS`. What we mean by this is that the port must "
"not set the value of this variable absolutely, overriding the existing "
"value. Instead, it may append whatever values it needs to the existing "
"value. This is so that build options that affect all ports can be set "
"globally."
msgstr ""
"El puerto debe respetar <varname>CFLAGS</varname>. Lo que queremos decir con "
"esto es que el puerto no debe establecer el valor de esta variable en "
"absoluto, anulando el valor existente. En su lugar, puede agregar los "
"valores que necesite al valor existente. Esto es para que las opciones de "
"construcción que afectan a todos los puertos se puedan configurar "
"globalmente."

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:191
msgid ""
"If it does not, please add `NO_PACKAGE=ignores cflags` to the [."
"filename]#Makefile#."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:193
msgid ""
"Here is an example of a [.filename]#Makefile# respecting `CFLAGS`. Note the `"
"+=`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:197
#, no-wrap
msgid "CFLAGS+= -Wall -Werror\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:200
msgid "Here is an example which does not respect `CFLAGS`:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:204
#, no-wrap
msgid "CFLAGS= -Wall -Werror\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:207
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"`CFLAGS` is defined on FreeBSD systems in [.filename]#/etc/make.conf#. The "
"first example appends additional flags to `CFLAGS`, preserving any system-"
"wide definitions. The second example clobbers anything previously defined."
msgstr ""
"<varname>CFLAGS</varname>se define en los sistemas FreeBSD en <filename>/etc/"
"make.conf</filename>. El primer ejemplo agrega indicadores adicionales a "
"<varname>CFLAGS</varname>, preservando las definiciones de todo el sistema. "
"El segundo ejemplo golpea cualquier cosa previamente definida."

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:209
msgid ""
"Remove optimization flags from the third party [.filename]##Makefile##s. The "
"system `CFLAGS` contains system-wide optimization flags. An example from an "
"unmodified [.filename]#Makefile#:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:213
#, no-wrap
msgid "CFLAGS= -O3 -funroll-loops -DHAVE_SOUND\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:216
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Using system optimization flags, the [.filename]#Makefile# would look "
"similar to this example:"
msgstr ""
"Utilizando indicadores de optimización del sistema, <filename>Makefile</"
"filename> se vería similar a este ejemplo:"

#. type: delimited block . 4
#: documentation/content/en/books/porters-handbook/porting-dads/chapter.adoc:220
#, no-wrap
msgid "CFLAGS+= -DHAVE_SOUND\n"
msgstr ""

